definition.value: A primary aliphatic amine that is butan-1-amine carrying a methyl substituent at position 3.
A pyrimidine nucleoside derived from the formal condensation of the N(1)-nitrogen of 4-amino-5-methylcytosine with 2,5-anhydro-4-(hydroxymethyl)-alpha-L-lyxofuranose.
A L-fructofuranose with a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
A dehydrovomifoliol that has S-configuration at the chiral centre.
A branched-chain saturated fatty acid consisting of tridecanoic acid carrying a 12-methyl group.
A L-leucine derivative that is L-leucine substituted by an oxo group at position 5.
An aminopyrimidine in which a pyrimidine nucleus is substituted with amino groups at C-2 and C-4.
A glycoside resulting from attachment of a dodecyl group to the reducing-end anomeric centre of a beta-maltose molecule.

The monomethanesulfonic acid salt of delavirdine, a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor with activity specific for HIV-1. Viral resistance emerges rapidly when delavirdine is used alone, so it is therefore used (as the methanesulfonic acid salt) with other antiretrovirals for combination therapy of HIV infection.
